**Solution 2**: thanks to this [post][1] by cbmbbz which is the most voted. The basic idea is, keep a hashmap which stores the characters in string as keys and their positions as values, and keep two pointers which define the potential max substring(*window* using my word). move the right pointer to scan through the string , and meanwhile update the hashmap. If the character is already in the hashmap, then move the left pointer to the right of the same character last found. Note that the two pointers can only move forward.

To understand *l=max(l,window[s[r]]+1)* is the key here:

If position of last found char same as s[*r*] is beyond *l*, which means the window will have two same chars s[*r*] now, so we need to move forward *l* to shrink the window. Otherwise, l stays the same. That's all what	 says. Your feedback or any thought is welcome. I really learnt a lot from all you genius.

