* Make a another copy of given array and sort it.
* Start iterating on both array from both directions forward and backward in order to get index of both side ( index at which values of both arrays differs ).
* if both index are equal then given array had already sorted.
* else number of element within that segment will become our answer (why ?? because of these element array is unordered , also it always gives mininum length subarray). 

  **Time - O(NLogN)
Space - O(N)**


