The idea is trying to find the left boundary and right boundary separately.
The right boundary .is set when the current number is less than max of what is encountered until now (meaning that if it was increasing then current is always greater than max)... also even if its increasing, its less than previous max makes it the new end.

The left boundary logic is similar but the opposite of the right boundary.

```
class Solution {
    public int findUnsortedSubarray(int[] nums) {
        if(nums == null) {
            return 0;
        }
        if(nums.length == 1 || nums.length ==0 ) {
            return 0;
        }

        int l = nums.length;
        int start = 0;
        int end = 0;

        int max = nums[0];
        int min = nums[l-1];

        for( int i = 1 ; i < l ;i ++) {
            if(nums[i] < max) {
                end = i;            
            }
            max = Math.max(max, nums[i]);
        }   
        for(int i = l -1 ; i >=0 ; i--) {
            if(nums[i] > min) {
                start = i;
            }
            min = Math.min(min, nums[i]);
        }
        return start != end ? end - start + 1 : 0;
    }
}
```

