                  0  1  2  3  4  5  6  7  (indexes)
                        i        i

    At step 2 & 4, we will assume that maybe it's the "last value which is not increased".
    so we will store their current "i" in the variable "end" if the condition passed.
    (if nums[i] < maxSoFar) -> if nums[i] less than all of its left side values.

    Now think reversely for finding the 'starting index' from where the sorting should start.
    nums[7] is the maximum value, so nums[6] is obviously less than nums[7]? 
    similarly nums[5] < nums[6] for an increasing array......
