The idea is to remember what was the previous shortest subarray `[l, r]` to be sorted. If a new wrongly placed element appears `nums[i]`, we just need to extend the interval to the right `r=i` and if `nums[i] < nums[l-1]` also to the left. 
```
class Solution:
    def findUnsortedSubarray(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:
        l = r = -1
        max_val = nums[0]
        for i in range(1, len(nums)):
            if max_val <= nums[i]:
                max_val = nums[i]
            else:
                r = i
                if l == -1:
                    l = i - 1
                while (l > 0) and (nums[l-1] > nums[i]):
                    l -= 1
        return r - l + 1 if l != r else 0
```

