In this solution we will first find the minimum and maximum number which is out of order and then figure out the correct index for them, then finally return the difference between the index+1.

```
class Solution {
    public int findUnsortedSubarray(int[] nums) {
        if(nums.length == 0 || nums.length == 1) return 0;

        // Min and Max value out of order
        int minOutOfOrder = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        int maxOutOfOrder = Integer.MIN_VALUE;

        for(int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++){
            int curr = nums[i];
			// Check adjacent values are in order 
            if(isOutOfOrder(i, curr, nums)){
                minOutOfOrder = Math.min(minOutOfOrder, curr);
                maxOutOfOrder = Math.max(maxOutOfOrder, curr);
            }
        }

        if(minOutOfOrder == Integer.MAX_VALUE) return 0;

        // Index where minOutOfOrder & maxOutOfOrder actually belongs
        int minOutOfOrderIdx = 0;
        int maxOutOfOrderIdx = nums.length - 1;

        while(minOutOfOrder >= nums[minOutOfOrderIdx]) minOutOfOrderIdx++;
        while(maxOutOfOrder <= nums[maxOutOfOrderIdx]) maxOutOfOrderIdx--;

        return maxOutOfOrderIdx - minOutOfOrderIdx+1;
    }

    public boolean isOutOfOrder(int i, int num, int[] nums) {
		// For first item
        if(i == 0) return num > nums[i+1];
		// For last item
        if(i == nums.length -1) return num < nums[i-1];
        return num > nums[i+1] || num < nums[i-1];
    }
}
```

