solutions.content:
The basic Idea is to do 3 steps: 
1. **calculate the minimum element** by looping **from left to right**, whenever there is an element that is not *smaller* than everything on its *right*, that element breaks the sorting, and thus its index is the `start` index of the ans. 
`more formally, find smallest i where nums[i] < nums[j] && i > j`
2. **calculate the maximum element** by looping **from right to left**, whenever there is an element that is not *larger* than everything on its *left*, that element breaks the sorting, and thus its index is the `end` index of the ans.
`more formally, find largest i where nums[i] > nums[j] && i < j`
3. `return end - start + 1`

```
int findUnsortedSubarray(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        // 1. find the first i where nums[i] < nums[j] && i > j; start = j
        // 2. find the last i where nums[i] > nums[j] && i < j; end = j
        // ans = end - start + 1;

        // start and end are set this way so that by default, ans = end - start + 1 = 0
        int start = 0, end = -1;

        // 1. find the first i where nums[i] < nums[j] && i > j; start = j
        int min_ = INT_MAX;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) 
            if (nums[n-i-1] <= min_) min_ = nums[n-i-1];
            else  start = n-i-1;

        // 2. find the last i where nums[i] > nums[j] && i < j; end = j
        int max_ = INT_MIN;
        for (int i = 0 ; i < n; i++)
            if (nums[i] >= max_) max_ = nums[i];
            else end = i;

        return end - start + 1;
    }
```

