2. O(n). Key observation: For a number x , if there is a number y smaller than x on its right, then y needs to be moved before x in sorted order. So the leftmost x is the left boundary of the unsorted array. Similarly, for a numbrer a,  if there is a number b larger than a on its left, then b needs to be moved after a in sorted order. So the rightmost a is the right boundary of the unsorted array.
