**Okay so here we need to find the start and end position of unsorted array**
easy way to do it is using sorting, you can find the solution in the discussion section
but that's a O(nlogn) solution due to sorting
Here, let's discuss the O(n) solution.
we need 2 for loops to find the start and end positions of the unsorted array( ie, st and end in the code)
**to find end**
we iterate the array form i =0 to n. and keep on calculating and updating the maximum value encountered till now.
So if we find nums[i]<the maximum then it is part of unsorted array and update the value of end and as we do it till i=n so we get the last value.
**to find start**
similarly to find start, we start form i=n-1 to 0, and keep on calculating the minimum value encountered and if nums[i]>minimum then update start
now calculate the length by you know how and accepted! 
**Time complexity: O(N)+O(N)=O(N)
   Space complexity : O(1)
   Hit the upvote if you liked the solution**
```
class Solution {
public:
    int findUnsortedSubarray(vector<int>& nums) 
    {
        int n=nums.size();
        int mx=nums[0];
        int st=-1,end=-1;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            mx=max(mx,nums[i]);
            if(nums[i]<mx)
                end=i;
        }
        int mn=nums[n-1];
        for(int i=n-1;i>=0;i--)
        {
            mn=min(mn,nums[i]);
            if(nums[i]>mn)
                st=i;
        }
    return (st<0?0:end-st+1);
    }
};
```

